        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 4:19PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 419 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Chesterhill. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stockport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
